      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUST IN CASEY (1) comes off an average performance last start when fifth at Sandown over 595m behind Moonlight Miller (34.72) in a Grade 5. Placed at her previous run. Better than last start and worth following up. PAW FORTRESS (4) is progressing well and looks close to another win after hitting the frame from Box 4 last run (34.82) at this track. Is yet to miss the placings from this draw, including three wins, from six starts. Will give a great sight again. PAW YOCHELLE (3) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Finished third (34.57) at this track last time making it two minors on end. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Will give a great sight again. KING RON (2) can sneak into the finish.",
